In this study, RH residues were used as a natural and cheap bio-source to fabricate SiO2NPs with control of morphology, phase, and purity. This was done by following two different routes of calcination of RH, the first at a temperature of 600°C and the other at 700°C, in the presence and absence of citric acid. Afterward, the extraction of silica from RH ash by dissolving it with sodium hydroxide and converting it to sodium silicate was carried out (Eq. 2). It was then precipitated again by neutralizing it to pH 7 with an aqueous solution of hydrochloric acid (Eq. 3) [34].22NaOH(aq)+2SiO2(s)→Na2SiO3(aq)+H2O\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
